	     <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%" >
	     <form action="/cgi-bin/mrate.pl" name="f109333905167213">
	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="/db/item.html?item=2003&amp;mid=109333905167213">Sirulus 2 Brother Qwinn 0</a> <a id="fs8" href="/db/item.html?item=2003&amp;mid=109333905167213#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Tue, Aug 24th 5:17 AM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=191870"><span id=" ">Sirulus</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">60 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Default [2.26]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Kinda late I know but... soloed Brother Qwinn for it. It is a fast but intense fight. I am a level 65th mage on Tunare server and my tactic was to park my pet at Brother Drash then wait for Brother Qwinn to path near (after verifying the second time he was up on my bard bot; the first time I killed him a random ranger in zone pulled him to the zonein to Splitpaw). From there I cast mala on him and sent my pet. I followed up with my Host of the Elements immediately as well as chaining Planar Renewal and Transons Elemental Renewal. On the first fight I had to use LoH at 53% on Brother Qwinn because I mistimed a heal (quads) and still ended the fight at 35-40% mana. He did not run until he was at 9% hp.<br/><br/>Pet buffs was Burnout 5, Protection of Calliav, Maelstrom of Ro and Velocity (for when he ran). I equipped the pet with 2 swords, a muzzle and girdle. The fight as I said is short but intense due to the unpredictable quads. The second time went much the same way except he quadded my pet about 4 times in a row which made him enrage. When trying to switch pets at 15% I mistimed my unsuspending of my reserve pet and Brother Qwinn summoned me. He did however run off after doing so which leads me to believe he will run at 19% if he isnt engaged on someone/thing.<br/><br/>The first kill only had a tunic and headband, the second was tunic, headband and robe. Good luck on your quest, I'm off to get some pipes!<br/><br/><br/><br/>-§ir</p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br /><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=574532 target=akztarg>Magus Sirulus Delon ~ Tunare</a><br/><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=790527 target=akztarg>Annihilator Cylint Nyte ~ Tunare</a><br/><a href=HTTP://eq2players.station.sony.com/en/pplayer.vm?characterId=107886102 target=akztarg>Cylint Hunter of Elementals</a><br/><a href=HTTP://eq2players.station.sony.com/en/player.vm?characterId=190420102 target=akztarg>Apox</a> Extremely fast food - Because you can't eat what you can't catch</td></tr>
