	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=10319"><span id=" ">Aelwulf</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">32 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.40]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Just for those who like the viewpoints from as many people as possible here's the route I took (just finished it):<br/><br/>Headband &amp; Sash were done, I dunno, by lvl 25 latest?&nbsp;&nbsp;Fairly easy.<br/><br/>I camped Targin on &amp; off for a week or two.  It wasn't really a regular camp, mostly watching for him while I solo'd kobolds for xp (this starting around lvl 44).  I think he was up once while I was doing this but a group already had him.  I was in a guild xp group in the King room when he popped &amp; dropped.  I'm 45 or 46 by now.  I'd say maybe, ehhh, 20-30 hours for Targin there not sitting in the room constantly.<br/><br/>After Targin (and some cursor bug issues that still aren't fuly resolved) I went to LGuk for Raster at lvl 47.  Got down there, another Monk with a Cleric were there but let me have the camp as apparently the Monk had just gotten Raster a couple of hours ago.  I figured then I'd be here least a couple of days.  I sat there with a lvl 34 guildmate (not grouped, he still has decent Live faction) for about 6 hours total.  Raster popped the one time I wasnt' watchng my spawn timer.  Took him down with some help from the 34 Pally with me (didn't pooch his faction with one kill).  Just for note, throughout this I don't play a twinked Monk.  I really have an issue with those &amp; I play things as straight-forard as possible.  I find it much more rewarding even if I'm not lvl 60 in 3 hours.  I do have a couple of decent weapons given to me but I did this with fists.  so total Raster camp time was 6 hours.<br/><br/>Then got some help from a Druid &amp; a Ranger int he guild, we hopped over to SK &amp; tracked Brother Qwinn, handed in items, took about 10-15 minutes.<br/><br/>Went to Rathe Mtns.  Brother Zephyl didn't spawn after 5+ hours straight of killing placeholders.  The 'A drake' spawned quite a lot, think we killed it least 10-15 times.  Killed Maldyl twice.  Others in zone killed the drake a couple of times &amp; I think Maldyl once.  Never saw HAsten either.  Had my little Druid tracking (same account, I can't 2-box it), the aforementioned Drid &amp; Ranger tracking until they had to log, then another Ranger helping later on.<br/><br/>I logged in today, and not only was Zephyl up but so was Mortimer Syytrak (go figure, but no he didn't drop the vest).  So I got that done in about half an hour 45 minutes.  Kind of bad when the turn-in NPC takes as long to camp as one of the hunted NPCs.<br/><br/>Went to PoK, bought the Gather Shadows Scroll, &amp; made the Shadow Silk (yes it's the scroll, shadow wolf pelt, and a silk swatch, and trivials around 50-51...mine's 46 &amp; got it first time).  Then combined everything for the robe.<br/><br/>For Raster I didn't use any kind of special method or anything.  Once the room was cleared I just sat in the corner behind the PH spawn spot &amp; killed the PH, then the other 4-5 spawns that pop in &amp; wander into that room in the 10 minutes or so after the PH.  Then I sat there bored for 15 minutes.  Rinse &amp; repeat.</p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br />Harik Sarome<br/>The Wandering Monk of Xegony<br/>Soldiers of Fortune</td></tr>
